<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3009] ICV-style update of Memstore for single-qualifier and frequent puts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3009</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We had an internal need for a method to update a single cell thousands of times per second without having a &quot;versions explosion&quot; problem, and found that the code can be somewhat easily modified for that by reusing Store.updateColumnValue and making it accept byte[]. I&apos;m putting the patch here in case someone else finds it useful, and maybe it can eventually make its way into the source.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
